    "narrative": "Today's slate features several strong starting options, led by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (74.46). His inclusion at third base is a no-brainer, as he boasts a solid base projection bolstered by a favorable park factor (+6%) and batting third in the lineup. **Lawrence Butler** (73.47) also stands out, projected for a strong outing from the outfield. His score is significantly boosted by a favorable park (+10%), a dynamic platoon advantage against **Kumar Rocker** (4.32), and his likely leadoff spot in the order. **Jonathan Aranda** (70.19) and **Tyler Freeman** (70.33) are also recommended starts, both benefiting from their projected early spots in the lineup and favorable matchups against **Sean Burke** (4.47) and **Spencer Arrighetti** (5.10) respectively. **Brendan Donovan** (66.36) and **Cal Raleigh** (69.89) receive significant lifts from the projected batting order and matchup advantages against **Randy V\u00e1squez** (5.43).\n\nWe have a few situational factors to note. **Gleyber Torres** (56.91) is showing a risk of rain (36%), which could impact his performance or even lead to a postponement. Despite the rain risk, his projected batting order spot of #1 and matchup against **Seth Lugo** (4.53) still place him just above marginal. **Taylor Ward** (71.46) is another strong play, benefiting from a significant park boost and batting leadoff against **Eduardo Rodriguez** (4.48). **Daulton Varsho** (60.52) is a marginal start, but his projected batting order position and platoon advantage make him viable, especially with **Chad Patrick** (3.90) not being an elite arm.\n\nThe most interesting bench decision today is **Geraldo Perdomo** (53.71). He scored higher than several players in the starting lineup, including **Gavin Sheets** (58.79) and **Daulton Varsho** (60.52), but the optimizer opted against him. This was primarily due to the projected lineup for the opponent, meaning **Perdomo** was likely going to bat lower in the order or not play at all if the lineup remains as projected. He also faces **Bradish** (2.63), a much tougher pitcher than some of the other starters our bench players are slated to face. **Wenceel Perez** (52.24) is also flagged with a rain risk, similar to **Gleyber Torres**, and his lower score and projected batting order position kept him on the bench.",
